COMMUNICATIONS CLOUD
Configure and Customize Your Enterprise Sales Management Implementation

You can configure, extend, and customize your Enterprise Sales Management implementation in various ways. You can modify the user interface by cloning and modifying the relevant Lightning Web Components. You can also leverage other core components, such as Integration Procedures and Data Mappers, to customize your solution.

Add Buttons, Actions, or Fields in the Enterprise Sales Management UI
Your Enterprise Sales Management implementation provides a number of buttons, actions, and fields to enable you to easily navigate the app or perform various actions. As you use and customize your implementation, you might want to use new buttons, actions, or fields, in addition to those that are provided by default.
Core Components in Enterprise Sales Management
Enterprise Sales Management provides a library of reusable core components that are used as the building blocks for this implementation. Core components handle specific functions used across the various flows built in the solution. You can leverage these core components when you build customized solutions in your projects.
Use the Enterprise Sales Management API to Create Sub-Orders for Non-Member Offers
By default, Enterprise Sales Management uses CPQ APIs to create sub-orders for non-member offers. In the 234.4.1.900.449.5 patch, you can optionally create sub-orders for non-member offers using Platform Events and the Enterprise Sales Management API. This enables you to create orders for large enterprise quotes.
Activate Sub-Order Action Tabs
After you activate the sub-order action tabs, you can cancel, delete, or submit multiple sub-orders simultaneously.
Enable Rapid Attribute Configuration
Use rapid attribute configuration to quickly assign multiple attributes to products in the cart without evaluating rules and pricing with each change. For attributes without "has rules" set to true, the Update button isn't shown because such updates don't need rule verification, and for attributes with "has rules" set to true, the Update button is enabled. Sales reps can then click Sync to refresh and reflect an updated cart. Sync runs pricing and validation operations for the whole cart.
Configure the Enterprise Self-Service Portal
Set up the Enterprise Self-Service (ESS) portal based on your business requirements. The ESS portal is highly configurable, so you can create your own set of users and grant them necessary permissions and licenses.
Customize the Enterprise Self-Service Portal
When you've configured your Enterprise Self-Service (ESS) portal and added community users with the appropriate permissions, they can start using the ESS workflows. The portal is available with default configuration and functionality. Depending on your business requirements, you can customize the portal to provide specific functionality.
Customize Additional Quote Cloning Options in Enterprise Sales Management
When your sales representative clones a quote, the quote line items are cloned by default because Quote and QuoteLineItem are configured as the default objects to clone. The out-of-the-box configuration also contains related objects to clone additional options, including quote members, quote groups, product relationships, promotions, and discounts. If you don’t want to use these out-of-the-box additional options, you can customize them to suit your business needs by configuring the required related objects. You can also define the operations of an sObject while cloning its records.
Enable and Customize the Creation of an Enterprise Order in Enterprise Sales Management
Enable your users to create and configure an enterprise order. They can create an enterprise order from a quote to enrich it with additional information, including technical details such as installation date, router specifications, type of wiring required, and so on. Alternatively, they can skip creating a quote and create an enterprise order directly with all required technical information.
Enable the Update of the Quote Status When Enterprise Orders or Final Orders Are Created from Quotes
Enable your sales representatives to determine if enterprise orders or final orders were created from a quote, by viewing the quote status. Configure the StatusModelMappingConfig session variable as per your use case.
Configure the Main Characteristic Fields of Products in Enterprise Sales Management
Configure the main characteristic fields of products for enhanced visualization and selection so that sales representatives can view these field values in a column in the asset viewer. For example, for Business Internet, the main characteristic field can be upload speed.
Configure the Pagination Settings of the Asset Viewer in Enterprise Sales Management
Configure the page size and page limit of the asset viewer in Enterprise Sales Management.
Modify Your Extended B2BSampleApp Class From Winter '24 Onwards
From the Winter' 24 release of Enterprise Sales Management, if you extend the B2BSampleApp class, you're required to make certain modifications to your extended class—for example, to your extended custom class named "CustomB2BSampleApp". These modifications are required because the Software Development Kit (SDK) loading mechanism for this class has changed from this release onwards.
Use Your Custom Static Resource Instead of the Default ESMClassic Static Resource
Customize the style of your Enterprise Sales Management user interface. With a custom static resource file, you can change the color of tabs, the size of buttons, and so on.
Enable and Configure Grid View in Enterprise Sales Management
Configure the spreadsheetViewerConfig session variable as per your use case. Define the maximum number of line items that your sales rep can select on the Summary tab, the size of the data fetched in chunks, and the columns that appear in the grid.
Customize the View By Dropdown List in Enterprise Sales Management
To add options to the View By dropdown list, configure the ESM/CustomViewSetup integration procedure.
Configuration of Change of Plans in Enterprise Sales Management
With Change of Plans, your sales reps can change the plan (product) of one or multiple assets added to a quote.
Configuration of Location and Subscriber Topic Sets in Enterprise Sales Management
